        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 3:42PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 342 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Portland, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Portland, Salamonia, College Corner, Boundary City, Liber, Collett,
Bluff Point, Powers, New Mount Pleasant, Brice, Bellfountain, and
Como.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
